The paper deals with resource allocation and optimization problems in heterogeneous cellular networks, which are typically studied in the field of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The use of multi-user sparse code multiple access (SCMA) and physical layer security also suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed content caching and energy harvesting techniques are relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and control systems (cs.SY).
